# Excalidraw monorepo overview

This repo is a **Cursor Field Engineer 201 demo** workspace: Excalidraw stands in for Adobe-style web canvas editors. Session goals, evaluation criteria, and the live agent prompt are in `.cursor/rules/field-engineer-demo.mdc`; presenter runbook in `DEMO-RUNBOOK.md`.

Technically, this is a canvas-based editor (React + TypeScript + Vite). Think of it as the same class of problem as a web creative tool: document model, rendering, hit-testing, selection, undo/redo.

## Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `excalidraw-app/` | Vite app entrypoint — run with `yarn start` (http://localhost:3000) |
| `packages/excalidraw/` | Core editor: App, elements, scene, UI components |
| `packages/excalidraw/element/` | Element model, bounds, collision, selection helpers |
| `packages/excalidraw/shapes.tsx` | `getElementShape()` — geometry used for hit detection |
| `packages/utils/geometry/` | Polygon/ellipse shape builders shared by hit testing |
| `packages/math/` | Geometry primitives (`pointRotateRads`, etc.) |

## Debugging canvas interaction bugs

1. Reproduce in the browser at `http://localhost:3000`
2. Trace pointer → `App.getElementAtPosition` → `hitElement` → `hitElementItself` + `getElementShape`
3. For rotation/selection issues, inspect `packages/utils/geometry/shape.ts` (`getPolygonShape`) and `packages/excalidraw/element/collision.ts`
4. Run targeted tests before opening a PR

## Node version

Use Node 22 (`nvm use` reads `.nvmrc`).
